co2_revised_reason: MAT values from Salinization gave a reasonable range of temperature change, but due to concerns intrinsic to the proxy, which can underestmate MAT in places with high accumulation rates such as the Wind River Basin (Sheldon and Tabor, 2009), temperatures were scaled according to a regional relationship between MAT from salinization versus MAT from δ18O of 1.4. The regional scalar is based upon observations in Fan et al. (2011, GSA Bulletin) and Hyland and Sheldon (2013, Palaeo-3). Also, median CO2 and error bars recaluclated using PBUQ (Breecker 2013).
